!!!
%html{:lang => "en"}
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "content-type"}/
  %body
    %div{"data-role" => "page"}
      %div{"data-role" => "header"}
        %h1 .offset()
      #offset1{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c"}
        %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
          %span.name .offset()
          %span.returns
            Returns:
            %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#Object"} Object
        .entry-details
          %p.desc
            %strong> Description:
            Get the current coordinates of the first element in the set of matched elements, relative to the document.
          %ul.signatures
            %li#offset.signature
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.2/"} 1.2
                \.offset()
          .longdesc
            %p
              The
              %code .offset()
              method allows us to retrieve the current position of an element
              = succeed "." do
                %em relative to the document
              Contrast this with
              = succeed "," do
                %code .position()
              which retrieves the current position
              = succeed "." do
                %em relative to the offset parent
              When positioning a new element on top of an existing one for global manipulation (in particular, for implementing drag-and-drop),
              %code .offset()
              is the more useful.
            %p
              %code .offset()
              returns an object containing the properties
              %code top
              and
              = succeed "." do
                %code left
          %h3 Examples:
          #entry-examples.entry-examples
            #example-0
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Access the offset of the second paragraph:
              %pre
                %code.example.demo-code
                  :preserve
                    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                    &lt;html&gt;
                    &lt;head&gt;
                      &lt;style&gt;
                    p { margin-left:10px; }
                      &lt;/style&gt;
                      &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/head&gt;
                    &lt;body&gt;
                    	&lt;p&gt;Hello&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2nd Paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;script&gt;var p = $("p:last");
                    var offset = p.offset();
                    p.html( "left: " + offset.left + ", top: " + offset.top );&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/body&gt;
                    &lt;/html&gt;              %h4 Demo:
              .demo.code-demo
            #example-1
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Click to see the offset.
              %pre
                %code.example.demo-code
                  :preserve
                    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                    &lt;html&gt;
                    &lt;head&gt;
                      &lt;style&gt;
                    p { margin-left:10px; color:blue; width:200px; 
                        cursor:pointer; }
                    span { color:red; cursor:pointer; }
                    div.abs { width:50px; height:50px; position:absolute;
                              left:220px; top:35px; background-color:green; 
                              cursor:pointer; }
                      &lt;/style&gt;
                      &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/head&gt;
                    &lt;body&gt;
                    	&lt;div id="result"&gt;Click an element.&lt;/div&gt;
                    &lt;p&gt;
                      This is the best way to &lt;span&gt;find&lt;/span&gt; an offset.
                    &lt;/p&gt;
                    
                    &lt;div class="abs"&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                      
                    &lt;script&gt;
                    $("*", document.body).click(function (e) {
                      var offset = $(this).offset();
                      e.stopPropagation();
                      $("#result").text(this.tagName + " coords ( " + offset.left + ", " +
                                                      offset.top + " )");
                    });
                    
                    &lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/body&gt;
                    &lt;/html&gt;              %h4 Demo:
              .demo.code-demo
      #offset2{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c"}
        %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
          %span.name .offset( coordinates )
          %span.returns
            Returns:
            %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#jQuery"} jQuery
        .entry-details
          %p.desc
            %strong> Description:
            Set the current coordinates of every element in the set of matched elements, relative to the document.
          %ul.signatures
            %li#offset-coordinates.signature
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.4/"} 1.4
                \.offset( coordinates )
              %p.arguement
                %strong> coordinates
                An object containing the properties
                %code top
                and
                = succeed "," do
                  %code left
                which are integers indicating the new top and left coordinates for the elements.
            %li.signature{:id => "offset-functionindex, coords"}
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.4/"} 1.4
                \.offset( function(index, coords) )
              %p.arguement
                %strong> function(index, coords)
                A function to return the coordinates to set. Receives the index of the element in the collection as the first argument and the current coordinates as the second argument.
          .longdesc
            %p
              The
              %code .offset()
              setter method allows us to reposition an element. The element's position is specified
              = succeed "." do
                %em relative to the document
              If the element's
              %code position
              style property is currently
              = succeed "," do
                %code static
              it will be set to
              %code relative
              to allow for this repositioning.
          %h3 Example:
          #entry-examples.entry-examples
            #example-0
              %h4
                %span.desc Set the offset of the second paragraph:
              %pre
                %code.example.demo-code
                  :preserve
                    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                    &lt;html&gt;
                    &lt;head&gt;
                      &lt;style&gt;p { margin-left:10px; } &lt;/style&gt;
                      &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/head&gt;
                    &lt;body&gt;
                    	&lt;p&gt;Hello&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2nd Paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;script&gt;$("p:last").offset({ top: 10, left: 30 });&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/body&gt;
                    &lt;/html&gt;              %h4 Demo:
              .demo.code-demo
